The board may issue a license as a professional art therapist associate for a period of up to five (5) years to an applicant who has;
Completed the educational requirements for registration with the Art Therapy Credentials Board, Inc.;
Obtained a board-approved supervisor of record; and
Paid the required fees.

At the end of the five (5) year period approved under subsection (1) of this section, a licensed professional art therapist associate who has not completed the requirements for licensure as a professional art therapist shall submit to the board an application for an extension of licensure as a professional art therapy associate. The application shall include:
A plan for completing the requirements to obtain licensure as a professional art therapist;
Documentation of compliance with the continuing education requirements;
Reports of compliance with supervisory requirements;
Letters of recommendation from two (2) supervisors of record; and
Payment of an extension fee not to exceed one hundred dollars ($100).
